oofem.out
2D linear mass-transport on 100x100 mm rect, consistent capacity (verification vs analytical)
nltransienttransportproblem nsteps 100 deltat 0.05 rtol 1.e-3 alpha 1. nsmax 200 nmodules 1
vtkxmllattice tstep_step 1 dofman_all primvars 1 5
domain 2dMassLatticeTransport
OutputManager tstep_all dofman_all
ncrosssect 0 nmat 1 nbc 1 nic 1 nltf 1 nset 1
# Linear (constant k, constant c) transport. `contype 0` is the default and
# `m` / `a` are not parsed in that branch. Diffusivity D = k/(vis·c) = 1e-4
# m²/s. Run length 5 s → diffusion length sqrt(D·t_end) ≈ 22 mm, well
# below the 100 mm specimen height, so the far face stays at p ≈ 0
# (semi-infinite regime, matches p(y,t) = erfc(y/(2√(Dt))) analytically).
latticetransmat 1 d 1. k 1.e-4 vis 1. c 1. thetas 1. thetar 0.
# Saturated bottom (prescribed pressure = 1); rest of the specimen starts
# at 0 via the initial condition. Linear problem — Picard converges in
# one iteration per step so no BC ramping is needed.
BoundaryCondition 1 loadTimeFunction 1 prescribedvalue 1.
InitialCondition 1 Conditions 1 u 0. dofs 1 11 set 1
ConstantFunction 1 f(t) 1.
Set 1 allelements
#@grid 2dTM
#@mesher qhull
#@diam 0.002
#@perflag 2 0 0
#@thickness 1.0
#@rect 1 box 4 0. 0. 0.1 0.1
#@nodebc 1 face 2 min
